cutback v0.0.1 - System for smaller, more focused backups

Usage: cutback [OPTIONS] [CONTROLLER] [ACTION]
       cutback [OPTIONS] [ACTION]

  Cutback is a backup system with the goal of creating smaller, more focused backups by generating
  filtered file lists before archiving and keeping records of easily reaquirable files.

Arguments:
  options                  Command-line options
  controller               Controller to perform the action for
  action                   Action to perform

Options:
  -h, --help               Display help
  -v, --version            Display version
  -c, --config     VALUE   Configuration file path
  -D, --dry                Do not run system commands (dry run)
  -F, --force              Force the action (create even if resource exists, etc)
  -o, --output     VALUE   Output path
  -d, --date       VALUE   Date for the backup in YYYY-MM-DD format
  -i, --index      VALUE   Index for the backup
  -p, --paths      VALUE   Search paths
  -e, --excludes   VALUE   Exclusion path patterns
  -r, --paths      VALUE   Record path patterns
  -f, --format     VALUE   Format of the metadata file
  -P, --progress           View progress
  -C, --compress           Compress archive
  -S, --finder     VALUE   Finder command
  -a, --archiver   VALUE   Archiver command
  -x, --compressor VALUE   Compressor command
  -s, --checker    VALUE   Checker (checksum) command
  -R, --reader     VALUE   Reader command
  -w, --viewer     VALUE   Viewer (progress) command

Controllers & Actions:
  proxy                    help version create read update destroy verify manifest records archive checksum metadata config backup log
  application              help version
  backup                   create read update destroy metadata
  manifest                 create read update destroy metadata
  records                  create read update destroy metadata
  archive                  create read update destroy metadata
  checksum                 create read update verify destroy
  metadata                 create read update destroy
  config                   create read update destroy
  log                      read destroy

See `man 1 cutback` for more detailed information.
See `man 5 cutback` for configuration file information.

